Oven Safe Compatible with all cooktops and oven-safe up to 500°F (tempered glass lids up to 425°F) Quick and Even Heating Hard anodized aluminum construction allows for quick and even heating Promotes Browning Textured interior promotes browning and searing for exceptional flavor — and easily wipes clean

Stove to Oven to Table A versatile kitchen staple, the nonstick fry pan features a textured triple-reinforced coating that is ideal for browning and searing, with or without oil, and easily wipes clean. Safe for dishwasher, oven and metal utensils, Le Creuset’s nonstick is the choice for mastering flavorful meals from stove to oven to table.

Toughened Nonstick PRO FAQ How do I clean my pans? The pan is dishwasher-safe but washing by hand is recommended. Simply wash with hot, soapy water, and rinse and dry thoroughly. What utensils can I use with these pans? Gentle use of metal utensils is fine, but we recommend silicone or wood utensils to avoid scratching the surface. What are stay-cool handles? The hollow handles will remain cool on the stovetop. However, the handles will become hot when used in the oven.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Yes, it is expensive so try to find it on sale before buying but once you get it (or another of the Toughened nonstick pieces), you'll be every so happy with it's performance. I still use a touch of butter, EEVO or coconut oil for flavoring but the non-stick on this pan is fantastic making it a joy to cook with and super easy to clean after. We recently go an induction cook top and the pan's heat distribution is excellent. This size was actually purchased to complement a larger set with smaller pans in it.

reviews.reviewerName: Amateur Chef, Photographer, Handyman, AthleteAmateur Chef, Photographer, Handyman, Athlete
reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easily the best frying pan I have ever owned
reviews.reviewText: It was time to upgrade when we bought an induction stove top. After much soul searching I settled on Le Creuset. I bought the10 and 12 inch pan. I have had them for two months and used both quite a bit. Fantastic. Even heating. Non-stick but still browning well. Easy to clean. No warping. Very comfortable handles which stay cool. Simply very very good frying pans. Still look like new. Photo: Spanish tortilla, started in the 10 inch pan, turned into the 12 inch. Clean and easy release.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks good and anti stick
reviews.reviewText: This is a good looking pan. And super anti stick.I especially hate making omelets because they always stick but this helps with that. Very well made.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great for eggs, but bottom will scrape your glass top
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. The Good:* pan is a great pan for cooking eggs with a super slick surface* it is slightly lighter than most in this range, and a comfortable weight to handle.* comfortable handle, low angle, round and soft.The Bad:* If using a glass top surface, the sharp edges on the bottom will scrape your cook top (The direction say not to move pan while cooking) Right!? I don’t think that is possible.* The contact surface on the bottom of pan doesn’t fit any of my induction heating elements. It should be the same size.* The bottom of the pan is much smaller than the cooking surface, so food around the edges of the pan have less heat.For the price, you would think these little bugs would be worked out.I would not recommend this pan for cooking with glass top due to the scraping the glass causing damage over time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Stellar Cooking Performance
reviews.reviewText: Real person here! Ordered this pan via Amazon Used and got a $40 discount. $115! Score! Just a teeny little Nick along the top edge that you can hardly see. But not worth a dime if it doesn’t perform well. But perform it does. I have a ceramic top GE range. That’s always fairly slow to heat up. I have several other high-end pans that I always heat using a medium setting and then wait and wait. With this Le Creuset pro, it seemed the heat took less time. Not fast, but not super slow. That was nice but the real pay off was how well it cooked. My first use was breakfast with pancakes and eggs. I let it come up to full heat before starting of course. Added a drizzle of olive oil. The pancakes were nicely browned and perfect. The eggs were also absolutely perfect and of course slid right out. No clue how long it’ll last but I am very meticulous in caring for my gear so I expect a long life. I loved it so much. I went back in and ordered the Le Creuset Pro 12 inch stirfry pan. Full price. It just has to last a few years to have the significant investment make sense. Fingers crossed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Baby it, and it will stay awesome
reviews.reviewText: Wonderful non-stick pan. I've had it for about a year now and it is still non-stick and fries eggs like a dream. I baby this thing: No high heat, no metal tools, gentle handwash. I save the rougher handling for my stainless steel pan. It is pretty heavy...I can't lift it with one arm very comfortably, and I would consider my arm strength to be a bit above the average housewife.

reviews.reviewText: After researching and reading reviews I finally decided to order this pan. reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy, good non stick, excellent heat distribution
reviews.reviewText: As stated in title! We replace our old one after years of daily use. This 12” and the matching 10” are used every day and hold up well. The non stick is very good and non BPA. Heat distribution and retention is excellent.
